                Writings.</p>
        </arrangement>

        <!-- required for collection level; optional for lower levels -->
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">

            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>Correspondents include: Norman Hapgood, George Brinton McCleelan Harvey, Merle
                Johnson, Edmund Clarence Stedman, Melville Elijah Stone, and Charles Henry Webb.</p>
            <p>Writings and accompanying materials include manuscripts for &quot;The Quaker city holy excursion, chapter 36 of The gilded
                    age&quot;;
                <title render="italic">A Tramp Abroad, Sunrise on Mount Rigi,</title> chapter 29;
                Following the equator, unpublished portion of chapter 51; a note and seven
                photographs of Clemens depicting "the progress of a moral purpose through the mind
                of the human race&apos;s Oldest Friend," Aug. 1906; two autograph signatures written in
                blottentot; and brief notes.</p>
        </scopecontent>

